  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ff771ccdf4150419d9ff4d342b069aae, type: 3}
  m_Name: Page_04
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.Tutorials.Core.Editor::Unity.Tutorials.Core.Editor.TutorialPage
  Title:
    m_Untranslated: 
  m_Paragraphs:
    m_Items:
    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: Add the View
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: "The Lifecycle manages energy, but we can only see it in
          the Inspector. LifecycleView binds energy to visible light.\n\n<b>Steps:</b>\n1.
          Create a child <b>Point Light</b> inside Flora (centered at the object)\n2.
          Add Component: <b>LifecycleView</b> to the Flora root\n3. Wire references:\n\n  
          \u2022 lifecycle \u2192 the <b>Lifecycle</b> component on this object\n  
          \u2022 targetRenderer \u2192 the <b>MeshRenderer</b> on this object\n  
          \u2022 pointLight \u2192 the child <b>Point Light</b>\n\n4. Set maxEmissionIntensity
          \u2192 <b>5</b>\n5. Set maxLightRange \u2192 <b>10</b>\n\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\u2500\n<b>How
          it works:</b>\nEvery frame, LifecycleView reads <b>EnergyRatio</b> (0\u20131)
          from Lifecycle. It multiplies this ratio by maxEmissionIntensity to set
          the material\u2019s emission, and by maxLightRange to set the light\u2019s
          reach. Full energy = full glow. Zero energy = dark."
      m_CodeSample: 
